This request should be an improvement of an existing issue JIM-799. 

Currently, the [JSON Importer|https://confluence.atlassian.com/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=314449019] includes some JSON data example which can used as a reference by end user to prepare the JSON file to be imported to JIRA. However going through the examples provided, apparently the JSON data is missing data attribute, such as the user email, user groups, etc. 

Comparing with the sample JSON data which is generated when we export an issue to JSON, the mentioned user details are included in the JSON:
{noformat}
  "users" : [ {
    "name" : "admin",
    "fullname" : "admin",
    "email" : "admin@mail.com",
    "groups" : [ "jira-users", "jira-administrators", "jira-developers" ],
    "active" : true
  } ]
{noformat}

Hence, it will be great if we are able to provide a complete JSON data example that our customers can refer to.

