As a Norwegian user, i would like to *verify* import of CSV files with Norwegian characters correctly by looking in the log files produced by the import. I have tons of unpleasant import logs due to Danish/Norway/Swedish/French/German special characters.

The problem wasn't about importing, import works fine with Norwegian characters. It is about the import logs, it confuses me and made me think the import wasn't correct.

{code}
2012-09-03 10:00:30,327 INFO - Importing issue: ExternalIssue{externalId=autoid-5019499565331943393, summary=Tidszone skift p� 1234, issueType=1}
{code}

The {{p�}} above is Danish {{på}}. Although it is supported in JIRA, but import just spoils it. My CSV file is always in UTF8 so it is not a user problem.

